what is the name of the children's book about girls who find enchanted items in their old house this is a book i read as a child that i got out of the library i know the book is a chapter book and i probably read it when i was years old in the mid s i remember there was a tin that lost objects appeared in and perhaps some sort of invisibility cloak and ten league boots there was a scene in the book with a school play the plot was that the girls find the objects and they don't know what they are for it turns out that they were enchanted by a witch the book is quite old i am sure and perhaps out of print i really would like to find this book for my daughter so i hope someone remembers it it is called what the witch left by ruth chew it is out of print as you suspected but used copies are plentiful since it was a popular scholastic selection you can find it at amazon com http www amazon com what witch left ruth chew dp tag e The Lion, the Witch and the Wardrobe Land of Oz Magical objects in Harry Potter Hogwarts Anne Rice World Wide Web PHP The Pilgrim's Progress The Lovely Bones Scholastic Press Harry Potter and the Half-Blood Prince Harry Potter House of M The Wizard of Oz (1939 film) The Subtle Knife Bible Diagon Alley Kingdom Hearts: Chain of Memories Harry Potter and the Order of the Phoenix Return to Oz L. Frank Baum Charmed Baseball The Wonderful Wizard of Oz Amazon.com Tin Woodman Book Witchcraft Publishing Harry Potter and the Prisoner of Azkaban Wizarding world Tag Choose Your Own Adventure Discworld MUD Spyware The Hobbit Son of a Witch Macbeth Wicked Witch of the East Little Britain Beauty and the Beast (1991 film) Alice's Adventures in Wonderland The Life and Times of Juniper Lee The Little Mermaid (film) Scholasticism Legal research The Tin Woodman of Oz Cloaking device Infocom Diana Wynne Jones Newbery Honor Voynich manuscript Into the Woods Harry Potter and the Philosopher's Stone Monty Python and the Holy Grail Hansel und Gretel The Tempest (play) The 